tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Wait time,Value for money,
review:
As you enter the Clinuc, one is impressed by the cleanliness and  elegance of  the waiting room. Pleasing assistants who check on you and details,  give you protective gears -- head cover, foot cover bag,  gloves etc to protect you from gerns. 

 Doctor Swapnil, welcomes you with warmth and friendliness.  His tone calms your fears and puts your nervousness to rest. He examines your teeth with care and explains what's wrong with your teeth in a simple,  understanding and convincing manner.   He doesn't alarm you with bombastic terminology.  He breaks your problem in parts and makes it simple and gives clarity to the issue.  Very professional in approach and excellent diagnosis. . 

 The machines and implements he uses are in tune to the latest modern technology.  The interiors are very artistically done....the lighting and the ambience soothes your nerves and with light music in the background...one experiences a feeling of wellness and healing. The whole visit is experiential.  My family has been Dr Swapnil's patients for years  and we have no regrets only positivity and super healing that radiates from him.  Superb interpetsonal relations and nominal fees.  GO FOR Dr Swapnil's ortho centre. You will live it.

Regards

review:
Half of the procedure for RCT was performed by the junior doctor who was extremely rude. 
The experience of 14 years of Dr Swapnil for which you choose to visit him is not going to be available to you. ****** ** *** ** *** ***** ** ******* ****** *** ******* **** **** *** ********* ******* ** *she inserted in mouth a dental cap lying on table for long without cleaning it, and when I questioned her and asked if I can see Dr Swapnil, she was extremely rude and said I am also a doctor. ********* *** *** **** * ******* *** ********* ********* *** ***** *** *** ******** ********* *** ** ********** ** ****** *** ******* **** *** ** * ******** 

Apart from above, I have had bad experience where the doctor performed filling ** *** ***** ***** ******* ** *** ******* ***** however, it was corrected later the next day when I still felt excruciating pain. 

Overall I'm not recommending going here, primarily because if the doctor himself is not going to treat completely but handover to someone who is not the face of the clinic, it's not a transparent/healthy practice. Second, the unpleasant behavior of the Junior Doctor is completely unacceptable. 

The fee of the treatment is high (don't confuse it with consultation fee) and when you don't get commensurate expertise and behavioral satisfaction, it is a big No No.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review:
Bad experience as a patient. I did root canaling here in 2019 November. I had paid INR 10000 for the crown and was told that there is a 7 years warranty on it. From the very start, I had felt that the fitting of the crown was improper, and my jaw would not close completely. But the doctor told me that it will become okay with time. I regularly brush twice a day, and also floss regularly.

In 2020, the crown came out while I was eating. I never chewed anything hard or sticky, but it came out while having normal food (rice and daal). On consulting the doctor again, he fixed it, and said that it was rare for the crown to come out like this. He also assured me that it should be okay now. But I still was not comfortable with the fitting.

Recently in Jan 2022, the same issue repeated again. The crown came out while having normal food. On reporting again, the doctor said this was happening probably because of sticky food like Eclairs/chocolate. I told him that I never have Eclairs or chocolate especially with this side of my mouth. On asking for a refund, he simply said that unless the crown is damaged, no refund is applicable, and I should just visit a dentist whenever it comes out again. Now I am shifting to Bangalore, and if it comes out again (I know it will), I will again have to pay for the fix. There is no consideration for the hassle I have to face as a patient.

People should avoid this clinic, *** **** ***** ** ****** **** ******
